          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Trump accuses Ukraine</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/donald-trump-attacks-volodymyr-zelensky-ukraine.png" alt="Donald Trump launches a fresh attack on Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Donald Trump launches a fresh attack on Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky. Credits: BBC</p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Donald Trump criticized Volodymyr Zelenskyy for complaining about <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-02-2025-h1-1-being-excluded-from-the-us-russia-talks?source=website" target="_blank">being excluded from US-Russian talks</a> on ending the Ukraine war. He also suggested Kyiv could have prevented the invasion through negotiations. He added that a “half-baked” negotiator could have secured a settlement years ago. Zelensky responded by saying Trump was echoing Kremlin propaganda points and questioned his knowledge about the conflict.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        After the discussions with Russia, Trump expressed confidence in an agreement and hinted at a potential meeting with Vladimir Putin by the end of the month. He also echoed Moscow's calls for Ukraine to hold elections, questioning Zelenskyy's legitimacy under martial law. Zelenskyy defended his leadership, citing public support and accusing Russia of seeking his dismissal, and added that Trump is living in a disinformation bubble.
       </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
